  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;for the global campaign for aid transparency&quot;</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;Friends of Publish What You Fund seeks to foster greater openness and accountability in international development. In collaboration with Publish What You Fund, a UK-based public charity and other partners, Friends undertakes research and targeted advocacy to promote aid transparency in donor and recipient countries. Prior advocacy and technical support by Friends and partners has resulted in increased publication of aid data by donors. With this grant, Friends will advance three objectives: increase the visibility of aid data in partner countries; improve data quality; and promote use of aid data for budget planning and civic engagement in partner countries.&quot;</narrative>
  </description>
